        "title": "fix(media): recognize .m2a files as audio",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Maps `.m2a` filenames to `audio/mpeg` in shared media-core MIME detection.\n- Treats `.m2a` as audio across the related filename-based audio surfaces: voice-message compatibility, auto-reply transcription note stripping, webchat local audio attachments, UI `MEDIA:` normalization, and memory multimodal ingestion.\n- Adds focused regression coverage for the shared MIME helper and the sibling surfaces called out in review.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #23014\n\nRelated #23014\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\nNo direct maintainer request. This implements the `.m2a` audio behavior described in the linked issue and addresses the ClawSweeper review feedback on this PR.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: `.m2a` files were not consistently recognized as audio by filename/MIME helper paths.\n- Real environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout on Windows, with this PR branch checked out at `21441a60`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\nnode F:/ZPtarget/openclaw-pr92167/node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts --reporter=dot packages/media-core/src/mime.test.ts src/media/audio.test.ts\nnode F:/ZPtarget/openclaw-pr92167/node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-telegram.config.ts --reporter=dot extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.body.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot/delivery.resolve-media-retry.test.ts\nnode F:/ZPtarget/openclaw-pr92167/node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.media.config.ts --reporter=dot src/media/store.test.ts\nnode F:/ZPtarget/openclaw-pr92167/node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts --reporter=dot src/auto-reply/media-note.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/chat-webchat-media.test.ts\nnode F:/ZPtarget/openclaw-pr92167/node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts --reporter=dot packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/internal.test.ts\nnode F:/ZPtarget/openclaw-pr92167/node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit-ui.config.ts --reporter=dot ui/src/ui/chat/message-normalizer.test.ts\nnode F:/ZPtarget/openclaw-pr92167/node_modules/oxfmt/dist/index.js --check --threads=1 packages/media-core/src/mime.ts packages/media-core/src/mime.test.ts src/media/audio.ts src/auto-reply/media-note.ts src/auto-reply/media-note.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/chat-webchat-media.ts src/gateway/server-methods/chat-webchat-media.test.ts ui/src/ui/chat/message-normalizer.ts ui/src/ui/chat/message-normalizer.test.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/multimodal.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/internal.test.ts\nnode F:/ZPtarget/openclaw-pr92167/node_modules/oxlint/dist/index.js packages/media-core/src/mime.ts packages/media-core/src/mime.test.ts src/media/audio.ts src/auto-reply/media-note.ts src/auto-reply/media-note.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/chat-webchat-media.ts src/gateway/server-methods/chat-webchat-media.test.ts ui/src/ui/chat/message-normalizer.ts ui/src/ui/chat/message-normalizer.test.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/multimodal.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/internal.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n```\n\n- Evidence after fix:\n\n```text\npackages/media-core/src/mime.test.ts + src/media/audio.test.ts: 2 files passed, 99 tests passed\nextensions/telegram tests: 2 files passed, 46 tests passed\nsrc/media/store.test.ts: 1 file passed, 44 tests passed, 2 skipped\nsrc/auto-reply/media-note.test.ts + src/gateway/server-methods/chat-webchat-media.test.ts: 2 files passed, 30 tests passed\npackages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/internal.test.ts: 1 file passed, 9 tests passed\nui/src/ui/chat/message-normalizer.test.ts: 1 file passed, 32 tests passed\noxfmt --check: passed\noxlint: passed\ngit diff --check: passed\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: `.m2a` now resolves to `audio/mpeg`, is classified as audio, is accepted by voice-message compatibility checks, is stripped after successful audio transcription, is exposed as a webchat audio attachment, is normalized as an audio `MEDIA:` attachment in UI code, and is accepted by memory multimodal audio ingestion.\n- What was not tested: live Telegram end-to-end upload against a real Telegram bot/channel.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: I verified the Telegram source-level tests locally, but did not have live Telegram credentials in this environment.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): the review found `.m2a` was mapped to `audio/mp4` in the first patch and that several independent `.m2a` audio maps were still missing.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nWhich commands did you run?\n\nThe exact commands are listed in the real behavior proof section above.\n\nWhat regression coverage was added or updated?\n\n- Updated media-core tests to expect `.m2a` as `audio/mpeg`.\n- Extended voice-message extension coverage through the shared extension set.\n- Added `.m2a` coverage for auto-reply transcription note stripping.\n- Added `.m2a` coverage for webchat local audio attachment MIME output.\n- Added `.m2a` coverage for UI `MEDIA:` attachment normalization.\n- Added `.m2a` coverage for memory multimodal file listing and audio file entries.\n\nWhat failed before this fix, if known?\n\nThe initial patch only covered media-core and used `audio/mp4`. ClawSweeper identified that `.m2a` should be `audio/mpeg` and that sibling audio surfaces still omitted `.m2a`.\n\nIf no test was added, why not?\n\nTests were added and updated.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n\nFilename-based audio classification for `.m2a` attachments.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n\nThe patch only adds `.m2a` to existing audio extension allowlists and maps it to `audio/mpeg`, with targeted regression tests for each affected surface.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n\nReady for ClawSweeper and maintainer re-review.\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\n\nMaintainer/bot re-review and CI. Live Telegram E2E proof is not included because this local environment has no live Telegram credentials.\n\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\n\nClawSweeper's requested changes were addressed: `.m2a` now maps to `audio/mpeg`, and the related `.m2a` audio surfaces are covered instead of deferred.",
